      "settings": {
        "heading": "Learn more about the Lan Series",
        "content": "<p>Learn about <strong>14Cr14MoVNb powder steel</strong> — Xinzuo’s proprietary core steel and why it outperforms conventional blade steels. <a href=\"/blogs/news/powder-steel-knife-guide-14cr14movnb\">Powder steel guide</a></p><p>What’s the difference between <strong>67-layer and 73-layer Damascus</strong>? Understand how layer count affects steel performance. <a href=\"/blogs/news/67-layer-vs-73-layer-damascus\">67 vs 73 layer Damascus</a></p><p>At HRC 62, the Lan Series sits in the sweet spot — learn how <strong>Rockwell hardness</strong> translates to real kitchen performance. <a href=\"/blogs/news/knife-steel-hardness-guide\">Steel hardness guide</a></p><p>Protect your investment with proper <strong>Damascus care</strong> — simple steps for cleaning, drying, and storing your Lan Series blades. <a href=\"/blogs/news/how-to-care-for-damascus-steel-knives\">How to care for Damascus knives</a></p><p>Want the ultimate edge? The <strong>X05Z Zhen Series</strong> uses Japanese ZDP189 at HRC 65–67 for the sharpest edge in the range. <a href=\"/collections/zhen-x05z-series\">Shop the X05Z Zhen Series</a></p><p>Compare all series side by side. <a href=\"/blogs/news/xinzuo-knives-series-comparison-guide\">Full series comparison guide</a></p>",
